I don’t censor my impulses, I just don’t respond to every one of them. There are certain impulses that I consider too disruptive or potentially harmful to express in any context. 

This is less about censorship and more about a deliberate choice not to act on certain impulses. I recognize that my impulses are often rooted in ego, insecurity, or a desire for attention. When these impulses arise, I take a step back and choose to respond in a way that is consistent with my values and intentions. 

It’s not that the impulse itself is evil or inherently bad;
